    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.3-4_0001" />
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                <opener>
                <dateline>
                <address><addrLine>Skyrim Farm,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Rt. 6,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine></address>
                
                <date>Oct. 16, '52</date>
                </dateline> 
                
                <salute>Dear Dr. Kendrick:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Lyndal has heard the story of Mr. Stork and the Pickle Fork five times, and would have heard it more but for the fact that we've been having flu for a week. She says for me to say to you: "Many thanks for the story. I like it very much, and I think it pays to be polite."</p>
                
                <p>It <hi rend="underline">is</hi> a good yarn. We have not yet been able to read "The Holy Earth", but we are coming out 
                    <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS COLLECTION
                    UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                    COLOMBIA, MO.</note>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.3-4_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    of the shadow of the flu, &amp; soon we shall read the book aloud. Many, <hi rend="underline">many</hi> thanks for wanting to share it with us. You will hear from us.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Kindest thoughts,</salute>
                
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS COLLECTION
                UNIVERISTY OF MISSOURI
                COLOMBIA, MO.</note>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
